    "recap_headline": "Davidson College Athletics",
    "recap_text": "DAVIDSON \u2014 A four-run fifth inning, including\nForrest Lietz's\nbases-clearing double, put Davidson in front, and\nIvan Hoyt\nslammed the door from the mound in an 11-10 win over Gardner-Webb Tuesday night at Wilson Field.\nIt's the fourth straight win for the Wildcats, who improved to 8-7, while Gardner-Webb fell to 10-7.\nThe Wildcats led 4-0 after an inning, thanks to six hits in the first, but needed a spark after the Runnin' Bulldogs pulled in front with a four-run fourth.\nThat's when Lietz drove in three by doubling to left center, pushing the Wildcats ahead 8-6. Their lead grew to three runs twice, but Hoyt entered a one-run game in the ninth. He struck out the first two batters he faced on seven pitches, then forced a flyout to end it and earn his third save.\nLietz finished 3-for-4 with four RBIs, while\nFredy Diaz\nand\nScotty Edwards\nhad two hits apiece.\nGarrett Pyne\nstarted and threw two innings, allowing two hits and one earned run. Reliever\nSimon Yochum\nnavigated a one-out, bases-loaded situation in the seventh.\nUp Next\nThe Wildcats will open Atlantic 10 play at home against Fordham this weekend."
